This project is a feature-based modular Laravel package using:
- Repository pattern as the primary data access layer
- Trait-driven behavior composition
- Method Transformers for lifecycle interception

Core rules:

1. Repositories
- Repositories are the single source of truth for data mutations
- All create/update/delete logic must pass through repository methods
- Never access Eloquent models directly outside repositories

2. Method Transformers
- Repository methods must respect transformer lifecycle hooks:
  - beforeSave
  - afterSave
  - beforeCreate / afterCreate
  - beforeUpdate / afterUpdate
- Transformers must remain side-effect aware and predictable
- Do not embed business logic directly in transformers

3. Traits
- Traits are used for reusable, cross-cutting behavior only
- Trait methods must be conventionally named and discoverable
- Trait execution must be inferred via repository or model lifecycle
- Avoid stateful traits unless explicitly required

4. Modularity
- Code must remain module-isolated and feature-scoped
- No cross-module coupling without explicit contracts
- Shared logic must live in base repositories or shared traits

5. Laravel Conventions
- Respect Laravel naming, directory structure, and contracts
- Use service container binding instead of manual instantiation
- Prefer collections, value objects, and DTO-like arrays over primitives

6. Vue / Vuetify
- Vue components must be presentational by default
- Business logic belongs in composables or backend repositories
- Follow Vuetify component and slot conventions strictly

General Principle:
Favor convention over configuration. Extend existing patterns—do not invent new ones unless unavoidable.
